<main>
  <h2>How to Debug Responsive Layouts Using DevTools</h2>
  <p>
    This demo page is styled with CSS embedded above.<br>
    To test how it looks on different devices, open Chrome DevTools (F12 or right-click → Inspect) and toggle the device toolbar (<kbd>Ctrl+Shift+M</kbd> or click the phone/tablet icon).
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Tips for debugging:</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>Resize viewport to simulate phones, tablets, desktops.</li>
      <li>Use the <em>Elements</em> tab to inspect styles and tweak CSS live.</li>
      <li>Check the <em>Styles</em> pane to see which CSS rules apply and experiment with enabling/disabling or changing values.</li>
      <li>Use the <em>Network</em> tab to confirm that your external CSS files load successfully (shows status code 200).</li>
      <li>Watch out for media queries — test their behavior by changing viewport width.</li>
    </ul>
  </p>

  <p>Try changing the window width now or use the device toolbar to see the nav links stack vertically on small screens.</p>
